title: For Sale:  Yugoslavian M59/66 SKS
postcontent:
I'm selling my customized Yugoslavian M59/66 SKS. 

I started with a clean, probably never-issued, SKS, with matching numbers, then customized it by removing the grenade launcher and grenade sight, added an after-market flash hider, removed the bayonet and cleaning rod, then ground off and reblued the attaching lug.  I then added a rear scope mount with a JMT XTA Tactical 4x30 scope.  One can look through the scope base and still see the original open sights.  A correct and original sling rounds out the package.   The unused tool and cleaning kit is still present in the buttstock.

The SKS has a teak-wood stock, rubber butt pad, and a bright, shiny bore.  I will include all original parts that were removed during the customization, plus a comprehensive operation and maintenance manual.

This is one of the rifles discovered still in their original wooden crates, as shipped from the Zastava State Arsenal to the Yugoslavian military almost 50 years ago.  It is a beautifully-preserved example of classic European craftsmanship at its best.

It's a great gun, it's just time to get rid of one of my toys to buy a new one.  The sale must be a face-to-face, cash transaction.   If you see this ad, the SKS is still available.  I check my email regularly so you should receive a response the same day that you message me.
